The EGL Extension Wrangler Library (EGLEW) is a cross-platform open-source
C/C++ extension loading library. EGLEW provides efficient run-time mechanisms
for determining which EGL functions and extensions extensions are supported
on the target platform.

EGLEW core and extension functionality is exposed in a single header file.
EGLEW has been tested on a variety of operating systems, including Windows,
Linux, Mac OS X.

LICENSE

EGLEW library is released under the Apache 2.0 license.
